          <!-- Toronto Specific Notes -->
          <div class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Toronto-Specific Considerations</h2>
            
            <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-8">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Local Conditions Affecting Design</h3>
              
              <div class="space-y-4">
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Clay Soil Adjustments</h4>
                  <p class="text-gray-700">
                    Toronto's clay soil (50-75 kPa bearing) may require wider footings. The standard 450mm 
                    width assumes 75 kPa minimum. For 50 kPa soil, increase to 550mm width. Always verify 
                    soil conditions with testing.
                  </p>
                </div>
                
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Drainage Critical</h4>
                  <p class="text-gray-700">
                    Poor-draining clay increases lateral pressure on walls. The 200mm thickness assumes 
                    proper drainage. Without it, walls may require 250mm thickness or additional reinforcement. 
                    Always include perimeter drains at footing level.
                  </p>
                </div>
                
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Frost Protection</h4>
                  <p class="text-gray-700">
                    Toronto's 1.2m frost line is mandatory. Some areas near Lake Ontario may have different 
                    requirements. Unheated structures require 1.5m depth. Insulated shallow foundations 
                    possible but require engineering.
                  </p>
                </div>
                
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Building Permit Requirements</h4>
                  <p class="text-gray-700">
                    Toronto requires detailed foundation drawings showing dimensions, reinforcement, and 
                    drainage. Inspections required: excavation, footing steel, footing pour, wall steel, 
                    wall pour, dampproofing, and backfill.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

